        <h1 class="content-left green">Markdown Syntax.</h1>
        <p>Markdown syntax is a Text to HTML conversion tool. To see everything that you can accomplish with markdown visit the <a href="https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Markdown-Cheatsheet" class="class1">Markdown Cheatsheet!</a> <br> <br> Markdown allows users to <a href="https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Markdown-Cheatsheet#images" class="class1">add images</a> to their wiki, <a href="https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Markdown-Cheatsheet#headers" class="class1">format text and styling</a>, <a href="https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Markdown-Cheatsheet#tables" class="class1">create tables</a>, and <a href="https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Markdown-Cheatsheet#links" class="class1">add links</a> quickly. Markdown does a lot more but these are just some of the more popular uses. </p>
      </div>
