      <h1 class="content-left green">Free vs Premium Accounts.</h1>
      <p>If you navigate to your "Edit User" page (the little person icon in the top right corner) you will notice the <b>"Want to go Premium?"</b> dropdown box. This is where you can pay the $5 fee to become a lifetime Premium User. Why would you want to do this? Becoming a premium user allows you to create and manage an unlimited amount of collaborators and decide who gets to see your wiki. This can be very important if you are working on complex wikis that require more than one person to edit them or to hide a wiki from the public until completion.  </p>
